                            <comment id="15353576" author="svenmeier" created="Tue, 28 Jun 2016 19:23:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually the idea of this &apos;feature&apos; was to prevent unnecessary timeouts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4689&quot; title=&quot;Javascript timers not removed when a Component is replaced by ajax&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-4689&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-4689&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I think it&apos;s just easier to always add the timer when rendering the head. I don&apos;t see a problem with readding the timer now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
